Here is what happened over the past two weeks at MZLA.
=F0=9F=96=A5=EF=B8=8F Desktop

   -

   Exchange: Graph & EWS
   -

      Turned on Graph in Daily =F0=9F=A5=B3
      -

      Started Calendar! =F0=9F=A5=B3=F0=9F=A5=B3
      -

      Team splitting up a little to focus on Security & Panorama
      -

   Account Hub Manual Config
   -

      Back on track and hoping to deliver for 154. Lots of patches are
      landing this week after solid teamwork and collaboration with Design.
      -

      Taking the opportunity to refine ages old UX and enable Oauth2 for
      organizations that have been legislated to implement MFA in regions t=
hat
      are impacted by NIS2 and similar.
      -

      Working with the Support team to provide content that describes the
      options available.
      -

   OAuth
   -

      Still waiting for responses from:
      -

         Yahoo!/AOL
         -

      Heard back that server side changes are underway and will be landed
      soon:
      -

         Comcast/Xfinity
         -

         Yandex
         -

      Plan Bs are in place for each provider which provides functionality
      similar to previous years.
      -

      As the new PKCE Yahoo!/AOL client IDs make their appearance in ESR,
      support volume may increase so our response has been:
      -

         Updated support articles
         -

         Uplift preparation
         -

   Panorama / Global Message Database
   -

      Team steadily moving forwards and Brendan

=F0=9F=8E=A8 Design

   -

   Desktop:
   -

      Calendar: design almost complete! Prototype
      <https://www.figma.com/proto/dHBhjR7RFrbmQC0WcAhSq3/tb_desktop_2026-Q=
2_CalendarViews_v001?node-id=3D2196-15480&t=3D8kuTKwLHhhkr2Azb-1&scaling=3D=
min-zoom&content-scaling=3Dfixed&page-id=3D2196%3A15479&starting-point-node=
-id=3D2196%3A15480>
      -

         Topic box post
         <https://thunderbird.topicbox.com/groups/ux/T138723c621dd257d/uxd-=
07-06-calendar-redesign-update>:
         received positive community feedback, with users responding well
         to the cleaner layout, improved visual hierarchy, and clearer
event styling.
         -

            Feedback themes:
            -

               Date navigation, including the mini calendar and jumping
               across months or years
               -

               Calendar views and layout, including month, multiweek, and
               standalone window use
               -

               Event display, including multi-day events, overlapping
               events, and event colour options
               -

      Settings
      -

         Initial User Research community shareout
         <https://blog.thunderbird.net/2026/07/desktopsettings/>
         -

